the efficiency of decision-making units that can operate on variable scales or
have non-proportional relationships between inputs and outputs. Essentially,
the additive DEA model allows for a more accurate representation of the
complexities inherent in real-world production functions, offering a better
understanding of the efficiency of decision-making units in various sectors.
